<refmeta>
  <refentrytitle>my-gtemplate</refentrytitle>
  <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  <refmiscinfo class="manual">User Commands</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
  <refname>my-gtemplate</refname>
  <refpurpose>GTK Template Application</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
  <cmdsynopsis>
    <command>my-gtemplate</command>
    <arg choice="opt">--dummy <replaceable>EXAMPLE</replaceable></arg>
    <arg choice="opt">--help</arg>
    <arg choice="opt">--quit</arg>
    <arg choice="opt">--verbose</arg>
    <arg choice="opt">--version</arg>
  </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>
  <title>Description</title>
<para>
  <command>my-gtemplate</command> is a simple GTK application
  that can be used as a template for developing GTK applications in C.
</para>
<para>
  The template contains basic GTK application with meson build script,
  basic tests using glib test, an example man page, help page using
  mallard, and gtk-doc documentation, etc. are included.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
  <title>Options</title>
<para>The following options are understood:</para>
<variablelist>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--dummy <optional>EXAMPLE</optional></option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        This doesn't exist.  Just to show how an optional argument
        can be added.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>-h</option>, <option>--help</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>Show help options</para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--quit</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
      Force quit the application.  Any unsaved changes will be lost
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>-v</option>, <option>--verbose</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Show verbose logs when running. Use multiple times to increase
        log verbosity.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
    <term>
      <option>--version</option>
    </term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Show version information and exit.  This won't quit already
        running instance of the application.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</refsect1>

</refentry>
